orbade his son to become a After a short time his father sent him to the great cities in order that he be tempted away from the priesthood but even through these trials Saint Aloysius grew in his desire for the religious life and was strengthened in the virtue of The Marquis' plans were obviously failing so he con fronted his son Will you or will you not obey me and forget this foolish ness I will not father was the in evitable Then leave from my sight and don't return until you change your mind With tears clouding his eyes the Saint left the room to pray Tell me Lord what am I to do Tell me Tell me He knelt down to flagellate himself as he had done several times before but this time he was The onlooker rushed to the This at last brought the proud man to his The Lord wants him the Lord can have He gave his consent for his son to become a After some years at the end of the sixteenth century a terri ble epidemic broke out in All the hospitals were full and could house no more so the Jesuits opened their Saint Aloy sius did all he could in the hospitals particularly to prepare the dying for a holy Saint Aloysius himself contracted the plague from carrying and nursing the For three months he lay with a burning fever and finally on June he gave his soul to the Lord while gazing at a Let us invoke Saint Aloysius as our patron and imitate him in his humility purity and confidence in Saint Aloysius Gonzaga pray for Brendan Arthur Prayer is as necessary to a person consecrated to the service of others as a sword is to a soldier God Bless From Simon Lines Simon Shields Programmer Viva Cristo Rey MONASH UNIVERSITY COLLEGE GIPPSLAND Ph Switchback Fax